arb4j (0.99.9.9.9) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  [ Stephen Crowley ]
  * New upstream milestone 0.99.9.9.9: parallel Real.autocorrelation
    over lag strides backed by a ThreadLocal scalar pair, bidirectional
    Wiener–Khinchin cross-checks (IDFT of empirical PSD on the
    covariance chart, DFT of empirical autocorrelation on the PSD
    chart), Recalculate button driving both panels in lockstep, and
    JavaFX 26 / JDK 26 build target.
  * Switch JDK build-dependency and runtime dependency from openjdk-25
    to openjdk-26 (control, rules JAVA_HOME path).
  * Install every script under bin/ to /usr/bin via debian/arb4j.install.
  * Drop empty override_dh_install in debian/rules so the
    arb4j.install manifest is actually honoured (previously the empty
    override silently disabled dh_install and bin/ shipped nothing).
  * Relocate every bin/ wrapper to a real FHS layout. /usr/share/arb4j
    holds env.sh, class.path, pom.xml, version, shell.start, and a
    lib/ tree containing every transitive Maven dependency JAR. Each
    /usr/bin wrapper sources env.sh and reads ARB4J_HOME, ARB4J_JAR,
    ARB4J_NATIVE_DIR, ARB4J_CLASSPATH instead of computing BASEDIR
    from $0. The dev-only updateClasspath script (which calls mvn
    against a checkout) is no longer installed; arb4jVersion is
    rewritten to cat /usr/share/arb4j/version.
  * debian/env.sh.in, debian/install-bin.sh: new helpers driving the
    rewrite. install-bin.sh uses awk to redirect BASEDIR= and FMDIR=
    lines, replace `cat $BASEDIR/class.path` with $ARB4J_CLASSPATH,
    redirect -Djava.library.path and LD_LIBRARY_PATH to
    $ARB4J_NATIVE_DIR, drop dev-only $BASEDIR/build/classes from
    classpaths, and resolve sibling wrapper invocations through PATH.

 -- Stephen Crowley <stephencrowley214@gmail.com>  Tue, 28 Apr 2026 04:28:00 -0500

